{"questionId":"9070444","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Enthalpy changes depend on the number and type of bonds broken and formed.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>The table lists standard entropy, <em>S</em><sup>Θ</sup>, values.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://ib-questionbank-attachments.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/tinymce_asset/asset/4522/Schermafbeelding_2018-08-08_om_15.07.35.png\" alt=\"M18/4/CHEMI/HP2/ENG/TZ2/05.c\"></p>\n<p>Calculate the standard entropy change for the reaction, Δ<em>S</em><sup>Θ</sup>, in J K<sup>−1</sup>.</p>\n<p>CH<sub>4</sub>(g) + H<sub>2</sub>O(g) → 3H<sub>2</sub>(g) + CO(g)</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>«</strong>Δ<em>S</em><sup>Θ</sup>&nbsp;= Σ<em>S</em><sup>Θ</sup><sub>products</sub> – Σ<em>S</em><sup>Θ</sup><sub>reactants</sub>&nbsp;= 198 +&nbsp;3 × 131 – (186 +&nbsp;189) =<strong>» «</strong>+<strong>» </strong>216 <strong>«</strong>J K<sup>–1</sup><strong>»</strong></p>\n<p><em><strong>[1 mark]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9070444","referenceCode":"18M.2.hl.TZ2.5c","subjectId":"45-dp-chemistry-last-assessment-2024","title":"The table lists standard entropy, SΘ, values. Calculate the standard entropy change for the reaction, ΔSΘ, in J K−1. CH4(g) + H2O(g) → 3H2(g) + CO(g)","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"c","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Additional higher level (AHL)","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 15: Energetics/thermochemistry","15.2 Entropy and spontaneity","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 15: Energetics/thermochemistry"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}